Växjö las. 28-29, dito ’samt tf. aman. v. Gbgs BB 29, tf. andre und:läk. v. Stora Ekebergs sanat. 29-30, tf. prov:läk. i Borlänge o. Hallstaviks distr. 30, prakt. läk. i Norrköp. sed. 30.
translated:
Karner, Friedrich (Fritz), practicing physician, Norrköping, b. 3/1/96 in Bleiburg, Austria, son of Dr. med. Franz K. and Maria Pitschko. Married on the 26th of an undisclosed month with Karin Lundgren. Children: Birgitta Edit Maria, born in 1927; Fritz Göran, born in 1930; Anna-Karin Tyra Elisabet, born in 1933. 

Education: Graduated from high school in Vienna in 1914, obtained a medical degree there in 1921, completed a medical candidate degree in 1923, and a medical licentiate degree in Stockholm in 1928. 

Professional experience: Worked as an intern at the gynecology clinic in Vienna from 1919-1920 and 1926-1927, served as a volunteer assistant at the surgical clinic in Munich in 1922, acted as a temporary assistant physician at the Carlanderska Hospital in 1928, worked as an assistant physician at Växjö Hospital from 1928-1929, served as a temporary assistant and trainee at the Gothenburg Maternity Hospital in 1929, worked as a temporary second assistant physician at Stora Ekebergs Sanatorium from 1929-1930, worked as a temporary physician at Borlänge and Hallstavik districts in 1930, and has been practicing as a physician in Norrköping since 1930.
